C_Search
Your goal pulls the night into shape, or at least gives you something to hold.

<<if $goalMode is "comfort">>You keep it simple and safe, no clock to chase. You scan for scuffed grit or a break in the snow without forcing a route.<<elseif $goalMode is "clear">>You and Malik work row by row, using the row posts as dividers. You brush away thin snow and look for disturbed grit, checking the clock so the deadline stays in view.<<elseif $goalMode is "quick">>You cut diagonals across the central path, hopping between older stones and smaller markers. The fog makes corners slippery, and you promise yourself you'll organize the evidence once the page is in hand.<<elseif $goalMode is "coauth">>Malik taps your shoulder at each turn and touches the fence so you don't loop. He calls out row posts. When you point at a likely spot, he nods and draws a tiny X on the page.<</if>>
<<if $cemStartChoice is "gate">>You start at the gate box and follow the scuffed grit you noticed on the way in.<<elseif $cemStartChoice is "back">>You start deep by the back wall and work toward the entrance, letting the rows guide you.<<elseif $cemStartChoice is "fence">>You start along the fence line and work inward, watching for the scuffed grit to cross your path.<</if>>
<<if $goalMode is "comfort">>Ten minutes in, you've looped the central path twice because you never set a boundary. At twenty, you slow down and pick one likely patch to trust.<<elseif $goalMode is "clear">>Ten minutes in, you've marked three rows to recheck. At twenty-five, a rust shadow lines up with the clue. At forty, the pale crescent near the gate box footing finally stands out.<<elseif $goalMode is "quick">>You save time now and spend some of it circling back when signs blur. Ten minutes in, you've cut three lines but can't remember if you counted the first one. At twenty, you slow down and pick one sign to chase.<<elseif $goalMode is "coauth">>Minutes pass, but Malik's marks keep you from wandering. At fifteen minutes he calls the time and points back to the last turn you logged. At thirty, a pale crescent of grit catches both of your lights at once.<</if>>

One pale crescent of grit stands out, but you still need a pattern to confirm it without losing time.

How do you press on?

