:: Tunnel_Entry_01 {"position":"100,1380","size":"100,100"}
Tunnel_Entry_01
It’s time to go now. You cross campus to the N Building, a brick block with a service entry and a faint hiss of steam in the cold. Snow falls gently, making everything quiet and eerie. Once inside, you find a concrete stairwell and a metal sign that reads ''Tunnels.'' The walk and getting the door unstuck cost a few minutes.
<<if !$overheadTunnelApplied>><<set $time += 6>><<set $overheadTunnelApplied = true>><</if>>

All the building lights are turned off. The stairwell is bare concrete and the handrail is slick with cold. The air from below smells like damp brick and old heating. Your phone light makes a small circle that looks smaller the longer you stare at it.

> ''Malik'' (hushed): Come on, before I remember I hate basements.

You and Malik creep down the stairs and shove open a set of heavy metal doors with a push bar. The corridor beyond is low and narrow, the concrete sweating. Water drips in a steady plink. The air tastes like mold, and Malik coughs. Machines thrum somewhere beyond a line of plastic sheeting and stacked cinder blocks.

The DEADline app sits open on your phone, pulsing red in the dark.

<<timelink "Enter" 1 "T_Setup_01">>
<</timelink>>


:: StoryScript [script]
/* timelink macro: placed in a [script]-tagged passage for SugarCube load order */
(function () {
  if (typeof Macro !== 'undefined' && (!Macro.get || !Macro.get('timelink'))) {
    Macro.add('timelink', {
      tags : null,
      handler : function () {
        if (this.args.length < 3) {
          return this.error('Usage: <<timelink "Label" cost "Passage">> [payload] <</timelink>>');
        }
        let label = String(this.args[0]);
        const costArg = this.args[1];
        const target = String(this.args[2]);
        const payload = (this.payload && this.payload[0]) ? this.payload[0].contents : '';

        const num = (v) => (typeof v === 'number' && isFinite(v)) ? (v | 0) : 0;
        const parseCost = (x) => {
          if (typeof x === 'number') return x | 0;
          const m = String(x).match(/-?\d+/);
          return m ? parseInt(m[0], 10) : 0;
        };
        const tryTwine = (expr) => {
          try {
            if (typeof Scripting !== 'undefined' && Scripting.evalTwineScript) {
              const opt = {
                variables : State && State.variables,
                temp      : State && State.temporary,
                context   : this.context || undefined
              };
              const v = Scripting.evalTwineScript(expr, opt);
              if (typeof v === 'number' && isFinite(v)) return v | 0;
            }
          } catch (e) {}
          return null;
        };
        const substituteVars = (s) => {
          s = s.replace(/\$[A-Za-z_]\w*/g, (m) => {
            const k = m.slice(1);
            const v = State && State.variables ? State.variables[k] : undefined;
            return (typeof v === 'number' && isFinite(v)) ? String(v | 0) : '0';
          });
          s = s.replace(/_[A-Za-z]\w*/g, (m) => {
            const k = m.slice(1);
            const v = State && State.temporary ? State.temporary[k] : undefined;
            return (typeof v === 'number' && isFinite(v)) ? String(v | 0) : '0';
          });
          return s;
        };
        const safeArith = (s) => {
          if (!/^[\d\+\-\*\/%\(\)\s]+$/.test(s)) return null;
          try {
            const v = Function('return (' + s + ')')();
            return (typeof v === 'number' && isFinite(v)) ? (v | 0) : null;
          } catch (e) { return null; }
        };
        const evalCost = (expr) => {
          if (typeof expr === 'number') return expr | 0;
          let s = String(expr).trim();
          if (/^-?\d+$/.test(s)) return parseInt(s, 10);
          let v = tryTwine(s);
          if (v !== null) return v;
          const sub = substituteVars(s);
          v = safeArith(sub);
          if (v !== null) return v;
          return parseCost(s);
        };

        const shownCost = Math.max(0, num(evalCost(costArg)));
        const timeHintRe = /\([^)]*(?:[+\-]?\s*(?:\d+|\?)\s*(?:[-–]\s*\d+)?\s*m(?:in)?s?\b|\btime\b|\bminute\b|\bminutes\b)[^)]*\)/i;
        const hasTimeHint = timeHintRe.test(label);
        let finalLabel = label;
        if (!hasTimeHint) {
          label = label.replace(/\s*\(\+\s*\d+\s*m\)\s*$/i, '');
          finalLabel = label + ' (+' + shownCost + 'm)';
        }

        const $a = jQuery('<a/>')
          .addClass('link-internal passage-link')
          .attr('role', 'link')
          .text(finalLabel);

        $a.on('click', () => {
          try {
            const V = State.variables;
            const live = Math.max(0, num(evalCost(costArg)));
            V.time = (V.time | 0) + live;
            if (payload) {
              const tmp = document.createElement('div');
              new Wikifier(tmp, payload);
            }
            Engine.play(target);
          } catch (e) {
            console.error('[timelink] click error', e);
          }
          return false;
        });

        jQuery(this.output).append($a);
      }
    });
    try { console.log('[timelink] macro registered'); } catch (e) {}
  }
}());

/* Principle HUD (playtest overlay) */
(function () {
  'use strict';
  jQuery(document).on(':passagedisplay', function () {
    // Disable overlay HUD, use inline PassageFooter HUD instead
    jQuery('#principle-hud').remove();
  });
}());